The paper presents a learning model for neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of computer science. The focus of the paper is on efficient use of on-chip data storage, which suggests a focus on hardware implementation and optimization. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves classification tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
